external_knowledge:
- A meal's popularity is considered high if it has a high number of orders and a high rating; 
- The 'first week of the year' corresponds to the period when the order date falls between January 1st and December 31st of the same year; 
- The 'most sought-after meals' are those that have the highest total orders in each category.

- Ongoing promotions refer to those with an end date in the future (i.e., greater than the current date); 
- Available meals are those with the "available" flag set to 1;
- Top-selling meals are determined by the highest total orders and total revenue.

sql:
SELECT AVG(checkout_price) AS average_discounted_checkout_price
FROM meal_prices
WHERE discount_percentage > 0;

SELECT promotion_id, discount_amount, promotion_description
FROM promotions
WHERE discount_amount = (SELECT MAX(discount_amount) FROM promotions);

SELECT average_rating
FROM meals
WHERE meal_id = 0;

SELECT meal_id, checkout_price, price_change_date, discount_percentage
FROM meal_prices
WHERE center_id = 0;

SELECT meal_id, center_id, AVG(checkout_price) as average_checkout_price, MAX(discount_percentage) as max_discount
FROM meal_prices
GROUP BY meal_id, center_id;
